## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="24f4d-117">Quando <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> viene restituito, è necessario eseguire il controllo verificando che il `pointer` parametro è `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24f4d-117">When <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> returns, you should perform bounds checking by verifying that the `pointer` parameter is `null`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="24f4d-118">In caso contrario `null`, è necessario chiamare il <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> metodo in un'area a esecuzione vincolata (CER).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24f4d-118">If it is not `null`, you must call the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method in a constrained execution region (CER).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="24f4d-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> le chiamate di <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> metodo ed espone il puntatore del mouse.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24f4d-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> calls the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method and exposes the pointer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="24f4d-120">A differenza di <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> metodo, rimane invariata la posizione corrente dell'indicatore di misura.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24f4d-120">Unlike the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> method, it does not change the current position of the pointer.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="24f4d-121">Il seguente exampledemonstrates come usare il <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> metodo:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24f4d-121">The following exampledemonstrates how to use the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> method:</span></span>  
  
```  
byte* pointer = null;  
RuntimeHelpers.PrepareConstrainedRegions();  
try {  
    MySafeBuffer.AcquirePointer(ref pointer);  
    // Use pointer here, with your own bounds checking.  
    }  
finally {  
    if (pointer != null)  
        MySafeBuffer.ReleasePointer();  
    }  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="24f4d-122">Se si esegue il cast `pointer` (che è un puntatore a un byte) come puntatore a un tipo diverso (T \*), si potrebbero verificare problemi di allineamento di puntatore.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24f4d-122">If you cast `pointer` (which is a pointer to a byte) as a pointer to a different type (T\*), you may have pointer alignment issues.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="24f4d-123">Deve assumersi la responsabilità del controllo dei limiti con puntatore ' this '.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24f4d-123">You must take responsibility for all bounds checking with this pointer.</span></span>

